{
  "texts": [
    "In this study we use the Monte Carlo approach to optimize the five key model parameters that have the strongest conditional interplay when applying the multi-STA/LTA method (sta, lta, sta and lta, and) as previously described (Fig. 2).",
    "Secondary parameters, which will vary based on the study environment (i.e., background noise and seismic signal amplitudes), include the trigger and detrigger values.",
    "These values were set in this study following a brief, visual-based analysis as this was a straightforward process.",
    "Whilst any parameter choices could be optimized through the Monte Carlo analysis, the visualization and appraisal process needed for the trigger values could become unwieldy.",
    "In general, the parameters that are used should be recorded and supplied with the resulting catalogue."
  ]
}